@page "/docs/components/image"
@layout DocsContentLayout

@using LumexUI.Docs.Client.Pages.Components.Image.PreviewCodes

<DocsSection Title="Usage">
    <p>
        The image component renders visual content and provides flexible control
        over sizing, object-fit behavior, and visual styling options.
    </p>

    <Usage />
</DocsSection>

<DocsSection Title="Width & Height">
    <p>
        You can optionally define <code>Width</code> and <code>Height</code>.
        These attributes are only applied if their values are greater than zero.
        This allows responsive images without forcing dimensions.
    </p>

    <ImageWidthHeight />
</DocsSection>

<DocsSection Title="Object Fit">
    <p>
        Control how the image should scale within its bounding box using the
        <code>Fit</code> parameter. This maps directly to CSS
        <code>object-fit</code> values.
    </p>

    <p>Supported values:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><code>ObjectFit.None</code> — no scaling, original size</li>
        <li><code>ObjectFit.Cover</code> — covers its container</li>
        <li><code>ObjectFit.Contain</code> — fits entirely inside container</li>
        <li><code>ObjectFit.Fill</code> — stretches to fill container</li>
        <li><code>ObjectFit.ScaleDown</code> — scales down if too large</li>
    </ul>

    <ImageObjectFit />
</DocsSection>

<DocsSection Title="Radius">
    <p>
        Customize the border radius of the image using the
        <code>Radius</code> parameter.
        This affects how rounded the corners of the image are.
    </p>

    <ImageRadius />
</DocsSection>

<DocsSection Title="Shadow">
    <p>
        Add depth to the image using the <code>Shadow</code> parameter.
        You can choose from predefined shadow intensities.
    </p>

    <ImageShadow />
</DocsSection>

<DocsSection Title="Blur">
    <p>
        Apply visual blur effects to the image using the
        <code>Blur</code> parameter.
    </p>

    <ImageBlur />
</DocsSection>

<DocsSection Title="GrayScale">
    <p>
        Apply a grayscale filter to the image using the <code>Grayscale</code> parameter.
    </p>

    <ImageGrayscale />
</DocsSection>

<DocsSection Title="Click Handling">
    <p>
        The component supports click interactions via
        <code>OnClick</code>, allowing images to be used as interactive UI elements.
    </p>

    <ImageClick />
</DocsSection>

<DocsSection Title="Custom Styles">
    <p>
        This component supports named slots (represented as <code>data-*</code> attributes),
        allowing you to apply custom CSS to specific parts of the component.
    </p>

    <p>
        You can customize the image by passing any TailwindCSS classes to:
    </p>

    <ul>
        <li><code>Class</code> — styles the root element</li>
        <li><code>Style</code> — inline CSS applied to the root element</li>
        <li><code>Classes</code> — dictionary for targeting internal slots</li>
    </ul>

    <CustomStyles />
</DocsSection>

<DocsApiSection Components="@_apiComponents" />

